-- Brazil to Raise Minimum Wage 9% to 678 Reais, Folha Reports
-- B y   D a v i d   B i l l e r
-- 2012-12-24T16:40:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-24/brazil-to-raise-minimum-wage-9-to-678-reais-folha-reports.html
Brazil’s minimum wage will increase
to 678 reais ($326) per month in January, Folha de Sao Paulo
reported, citing President Dilma Rousseff’s chief of staff
Gleisi Hoffmann.  The new figure, which would be 9 percent above the current
622-reai minimum wage, will be published in the official gazette
on Dec. 26, the publication reported Hoffmann as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Biller in Rio de Janeiro at 
 dbiller1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 